HEADWORD: Indiscernible
<hw>In`dis*cern"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>discernible</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>indiscernable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not to be discerned;
imperceptible; not discoverable or visible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Secret and <qex>indiscernible</qex> ways.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj></p>

